{"title_page": "Shaqilath II", "text_new": "'''Shaqilath II''' (fl. 70), was a queen of the Nabataeans.\n\n[[File:Malichos II silver drachm.jpg|thumb|right|400px|Silver drachm of Malichus II with his wife Shaqilat II]]\n\nShe was the daughter of [[Aretas IV Philopatris|Aretas IV]] of the [[Nabataeans]]. She ruled jointly with her husband [[Malichus II]] (40-70). After his death she was regent for her son [[Rabbel II Soter|Rabel II]]. Copper and silver coins where she is depicted with her husband, and coins of her with her son, have been recovered.  Some of these coins are dated with regnal years to the left of the queen.\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of rulers of Nabatea]]\n* [[Shaqilath]]\n\n==References==\n*[http://www.guide2womenleaders.com/womeninpower/Womeninpower01.htm\"Women in Power\" last accessed January 10, 2007]\n* Dated Coins of Antiquity Cohen\n\n[[Category:Nabataean monarchs]]\n[[Category:1st-century monarchs in the Middle East]]\n[[Category:1st-century women rulers]]\n[[Category:1st-century Arabs]]\n\n\n{{MEast-hist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Shaqilath II''' (fl. 70), was a queen of the Nabataeans.\n\n[[File:Malichos II silver drachm.jpg|thumb|right|400px|Silver drachm of Malichus II with his wife Shaqilat]]\n\nShe was the daughter of [[Aretas IV Philopatris|Aretas IV]] of the [[Nabataeans]]. She ruled jointly with her husband [[Malichus II]] (40-70). After his death she was regent for her son [[Rabbel II Soter|Rabel II]]. Copper and silver coins where she is depicted with her husband, and coins of her with her son, have been recovered.  Some of these coins are dated with regnal years to the left of the queen.\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of rulers of Nabatea]]\n* [[Shaqilath]]\n\n==References==\n*[http://www.guide2womenleaders.com/womeninpower/Womeninpower01.htm\"Women in Power\" last accessed January 10, 2007]\n* Dated Coins of Antiquity Cohen\n\n[[Category:Nabataean monarchs]]\n[[Category:1st-century monarchs in the Middle East]]\n[[Category:1st-century 